A Nairobi businessman has been charged with causing the death of a woman by dangerous driving along Jogoo Road.Bernard Kariuki was accused of speeding and driving in a manner which was dangerous to other road users.The prosecution says he hit pedestrian Felister Waweru at a zebra crossing and his vehicle veered off the road and landed in a ditch.Waweru suffered serious head injuries and bled profusely. She died while undergoing treatment.Kariuki allegedly committed the offence on November 20 last year at 6.30pm in Makadara, Nairobi.Kariuki denied the charges before chief magistrate Heston Nyaga and was released on a Sh50,000 bail or an alternative Sh200,000 bond. The case will be heard on May 8.